name: "paradise lost (part 2) 堕ちた楽園" limited edition print
description:
20x29.5cm print.
30.5cmx40.5cm antique white card mount, signed, with rigid card backing and wrapped in cellophane.

Shot on a Lomo LC-A+.

This image is created from film swaps with Hodaka Yamamato of Gifu in Japan. I shot a roll on the ‘normal’ side of 35mm film, rewound (leaving the end of the film still poking out of the magazine) and posted this to Hodaka in Japan. When he received the film, he then reversed and rewound the film, and shot the roll again so that the second exposure was shot on the ‘wrong’ side. When shooting on the reverse side, the image is ‘red scaled’ - all colours become shades of red, so the images are a combination of true and red scaled colours. 
Each image represents a journey – the UK and Japan fused into one to create both sides of the world in one image.

(To save on postage, it is also possible to collect from my home in Brighton. Simply type in COLLECT at the check out, and let us know when you want to stop in!)
